I. Reading Seurat object

First step is to read the Seurat objects, previously created

message("Loading Seurat object...")
## Loading Seurat object...
data.seurat <- readRDS(input_seurat_object)
message(ncol(data.seurat), " cells were loaded")
## 23179 cells were loaded
message(nrow(data.seurat), " genes were loaded")
## 23932 genes were loaded

Plot expression between 2 conditions

# Parameters
gene <- "ND-75"

# Prepare
boxplot_data <- data.frame(expression = data.seurat@assays$RNA@data[gene, ], annotation = data.seurat$annotation, condition = data.seurat$orig.ident)

# Plot
p <- ggplot(boxplot_data, aes(x = annotation, y = expression, fill = condition)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(x = NULL, y = paste0(gene, " normalized expression")) +
  theme_minimal() + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = tissuePalette)

# Save
ggsave(p, filename = paste0(output_figure_prefix, "_boxplot_",gene,".pdf"), width = 15, height = 5, bg = "white")
ggsave(p, filename = paste0(output_figure_prefix, "_boxplot_",gene,".png"), width = 15, height = 5, dpi = 1000, bg = 'white')

p
